  "course_description": "Selected topics in Music. May be repeated when topic varies.",
  "course_notes": "\"Blaxploitation: Music & Commerce\" The transatlantic slave trade formally ended in 1867, yet related systems of economic exploitation - particularly of Black cultural production - persist into the present. This interdisciplinary course examines the historical intersections of commerce, technology, law, and racism in the reception, dissemination, and control of Black artistic production. It asks: \"Who owns Black music?\" (Same as AAS 385 5)",
